data.value: To write a single object to an Excel .xlsx file it is only necessary to specify a target file name. To write to multiple sheets it is necessary to create an
ExcelWriter
object with a target file name, and specify a sheet in the file to write to.
Multiple sheets may be written to by specifying unique
sheet_name
. With all data written to the file it is necessary to save the changes. Note that creating an
ExcelWriter
object with a file name that already exists will result in the contents of the existing file being erased.
For compatibility with
, to_excel serializes lists and dicts to strings before writing.
Once a workbook has been saved it is not possible to write further data without rewriting the whole workbook.
